						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Bhramarēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Prajōtpatti, Vaiśākha, śu. 7, Monday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a gift to the temple of Bhramarēśvaraliṅga and also some renovation by Ālā Timma-Nāyaniṅgāru of Ārumūru, for the merit of his parents. Further it records the consecration of Raghunātha in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
